CommonFields.Title: Graphene oxide and base-washed graphene oxide as reinforcements in PMMA nanocomposites
Author: Vallés, Cristina
Kinloch, Ian A.
Young, Robert J.
Wilson, Neil R.
Rourke, Jonathan P.
CommonFields.Location: School of Materials, University of Manchester, Oxford Road, Manchester M13 9PL, UK

Mixing.Description: 100g of graphite powder and 50g of sodium nitrate was stirred into 2.3L of sulfuric acid
60g of potassium permanganate was added while the solution was agitated
Solution removed from ice bath, stirred at 35 Celsius, and then distilled water was added
2.8L of water and 50mL hydrogen peroxide slowly added into the solution

ChooseParameter.Other: The mixture was filtered and washed with 1:10 HCl solution (5L) in order to remove metal ions
Highly-stable graphene oxide (GO) dispersions were obtained, which were then centrifuged at 11,000 rpm to separate the solid material from the aqueous phase.

Drying-Evaporation.Description: The supernatant was discarded and the graphene oxide powder dried under vacuum.

Mixing.Description: The GO was suspended in a low concentration (0.01M) NaOH.

Heating.Description: GO was heated in NaOH at reflux for one hour

ChooseParameter.Other: After heating, the black aggregate wasseparated from the supernatant by centrifugation

Mixing.Description: The black aggregate was reprotonated with HCl of an equivalent concentration to the NaOH

TwinScrewExtrusion.Extruder: Thermo Scientific HAAKE MiniLab micro compounder

ChooseParameter.Other: The material was re-fed and cycled three times in order to obtain a good dispersion of the fillers in the polymer.

MoldingInfo.Description: Extruded samples were processed by pressure moulding at 180°C into 1 mm thick sheets and then cut to shape.

Dynamic_Mechanical_Analysis.Description: DMTA for the samples was performed in the tensile mode between 10 and 200°C using a DMA Q800 analyser (TA instruments). A heating rate of 3°C/min and a frequency of 1 Hz were employed under a nitrogen flow.

Thermogravimetric_Analysis.Description: TGA was performed at a heating rate of 10°C/min under nitrogen.
